Your understanding:
PART 1 (Backend API):
  âœ… Used when: Separate frontend/backend
  âœ… Frontend: Manages state (UI controls flow)
  âœ… Backend: Stateless services
  âœ… Cost: Higher (network, servers)
  âœ… Example: Modern apps, web apps

PART 2 (State Pattern):
  âœ… Used when: One system (cheaper)
  âœ… State machine: Acts as "frontend" (manages flow)
  âœ… Services: Acts as "backend" (stateless!)
  âœ… Cost: Lower (no network needed)
  âœ… Example: Embedded ATMs, vending machines

Key Insight:
  âœ… State pattern = Frontend concern
  âœ… Backend = Always stateless (both cases!)
  âœ… Only difference = who plays "frontend" role

